{
  "stem": "20021.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And nationalistic parties meant anti-Semitic parties, because nationalism stresses one nation and is against any ethnic diversity or any ethnic groups.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "All nationalists are against-- even in the United States today, that's the same story.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they were Jews, but of Polish extraction.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, anybody whose parent was born in Poland was suddenly expelled out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hitler issued an edict and took all those people, brought them to the border, and told them, you go.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Poles, whether they wanted to accept him or not, had no choice, see?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So many German Jews, young people born in Germany but their parents who had been born in Poland, suddenly had to return to Poland, to a place of origin, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many of them came to Tarnow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I came in contact with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But even that didn't awaken anybody to that reality, see?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Hitler always had an excuse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In this case, the excuse was that they were actually Polish nationalists.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They never became German citizens.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In other words, they lived in Germany under a special permission for years.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Europe, this was quite common.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Unlike in this country that an immigrant gets-- becomes a citizen after five years, in Europe the prevailing pattern was that people would live for 20, 30, 40 years as foreign nationals and keep extending their permit to live there.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was in France, in Belgium, in-- in Germany very prevalent.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they came into town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We talked to them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We faced their tragedy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were devastated.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
